Homex Development Corp: Class Action — Stock Fraud News & Information






























 






























  Free Case Evaluation : 877.238.4175 Tap Here To Call Us   







 
Stock Fraud News & Information

Published By Fitapelli | Kurta





           Stock Fraud News & Information         STOCK FRAUD CLAIMS PRODUCTS PRESS     












Published on: March 30, 2017
Homex Development Corp: Class Action

By Fitapelli Kurta






 



Publicly available records indicate that a class action lawsuit has been filed on behalf of investors in American Depositary Shares of Homex Development Corp., also known as Desarrolladora Homex, S.A.B. de C.V. (formerly NYSE:HXM) in connection to alleged violations of securities laws by HXM and certain of its officers. Fitapelli Kurta is interested in hearing from investors who have complaints regarding investments made in Homex Development Corp between April 30, 2012 through May 5, 2016.
The class action complaint specifically alleges that during the period in question, HXM and certain of its officers might have provided false and/or misleading material information, and/or failed to disclose adverse material information to the public, namely: that from 2010-2013, the company reported nonexistent sales of at least 100,000 home units, effectively overstating its revenues by as much as $3.3 billion, or 355%; that the company and certain of its Headquarters Financial Reporting Personnel willfully participated in a scheme to overstate units sold, revenue, as well as other items; and that consequently the company’s statements to the public about its business, operations and prospects were false and misleading and/or had no reasonable basis during the relevant period. According to the lawsuit, the revelation of true details caused harm to the company’s investors.
A class action lawsuit has already been filed in connection with Homex Development Corp., also known as Desarrolladora Homex, S.A.B. de C.V. If you wish to serve as lead plaintiff in the HXM lawsuit, you must move the Court no later than May 15, 2017. If you wish to join the litigation, please contact Marc Fitapelli at 212-658-1501 or Jonathan Kurta at 212-658-1502. There is no cost or obligation to you and your ability to share in any recovery does not require that you serve as a lead plaintiff.














Contact Us
FREE CASE EVALUATION TOLL FREE: 877.238.4175 LOCAL PHONE: 212.658.1500


















